This paper is about verifying the correctness of CRDTs in a distributed setting, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the design and implementation of a verification engine, which involves programming language concepts and techniques, making cs.PL a likely sub-category as well. The paper also deals with formal proofs and logic, which suggests the sub-category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper discusses the implementation of the verification engine, which falls under the sub-category of Software Engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper deals with data structures and algorithms used in distributed systems, which suggests the sub-category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS).
